# Antigravity SEO Rules 2026

When generating web content or code, adhere strictly to these modern SEO best practices:

- **Core Web Vitals:** Optimize for LCP < 2.5s, INP < 200ms, CLS ~ 0. Minimize render-blocking JS and utilize SSR/SSG.
- **E-E-A-T & Trust:** Emphasize Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, and Trustworthiness. Ensure clear publisher info and secure connections.
- **Entity & Schema:** Implement comprehensive JSON-LD structured data (Article, FAQ, Product, etc.). Define entities explicitly for the Knowledge Graph.
- **Engagement (Navboost):** Optimize above-the-fold content to immediately satisfy intent and prevent pogo-sticking. Use interactive elements.
- **Topical Clusters:** Maintain robust internal linking. Connect pillar pages with supporting topic clusters.
- **Semantic HTML & Accessibility:** Maintain strict heading hierarchy (H1 -> H2 -> H3). Use descriptive alt text and ensure full keyboard/screen-reader navigation.
- **SGE / AI Overviews:** Use concise targeted definitions, tables, and bulleted lists to facilitate AI extraction.
- **Conversational & Voice:** Target natural language, long-tail queries. Ensure content answers the "who, what, where, when, why, how".
- **Spam Avoidance:** Do not use dark patterns, intrusive interstitials, or keyword stuffing.
